flowRoot.flowPara: Thread support for Nimrod. Note: This is part of the system module. Do not import it directly. To activate thread support you need to compile with the --threads:on command line switch.

Nimrod's memory model for threads is quite different from other common programming languages (C, Pascal): Each thread has its own (garbage collected) heap and sharing of memory is restricted. This helps to prevent race conditions and improves efficiency. See the manual for details of this memory model.
Nimrod thread. A thread is a heavy object (~14K) that must not be part of a message! Use a TThreadId for that.
The current implementation uses a pointer as a thread ID.
Returns true if t is running.
Waits for the thread t to finish.
Waits for every thread in t to finish.
